# Form Layout

Every form is wrapped in a **DaisyUI card**. Inside the card, use a **borderless table** for fields (label left, control right).

Classes from `src/routes/layout.css`: `form-table`, `form-table-label`, `form-table-field`, `form-actions`.

```svelte
<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm max-w-2xl">
	<div class="card-body">
		<form {...remoteForm}>
			<table class="form-table">
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td class="form-table-label">Label</td>
						<td class="form-table-field">
							<input {...remoteForm.fields.name.as('text')} class="input input-bordered w-full max-w-md" />
						</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			<div class="form-actions">
				<a href="..." class="btn btn-ghost">Cancel</a>
				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
			</div>
		</form>
	</div>
</div>
```

Rules:

- **Card required**: `card bg-base-100 shadow-sm` + `card-body` wrapping each form (primary border applied globally via `.card` in `layout.css`)
- **Table inside card**: no `table-zebra`; borderless via `form-table`
- **Actions**: `form-actions` below the table — full width; one button spans all width; multiple buttons share width equally (`flex-1` each)
- **Responsive**: On small screens (below `md`), labels stack above fields (handled by `form-table` styles in `src/routes/layout.css`)
- **Required fields**: add HTML `required` on the control; labels automatically show a red `*` via `.form-table-label` styles. For composite required fields without a single `[required]` control, add `form-table-label-required` to the label cell.
- **Password fields**: use [`PasswordInput`](src/lib/components/PasswordInput.svelte) — never a bare `type="password"` input; includes eye toggle to show/hide
- **Sign up**: always include a confirm-password field; validate match server-side
- Hidden fields (e.g. `id` on edit): inside `<form>` but outside `<table>`
- Page title (`h1`) stays **above** the card

